context: An Islamist movement influenced by Salafism and the jihad in <a1_2>Afghanistan<a1_2/>, as well as the Muslim Brotherhood, was the FIS or <a0_0><a0_1><a0_2><b5_0>Front Islamique de Salut<b5_0/><a0_2/><a0_1/><a0_0/> (the Islamic Salvation Front) in <a1_0><a1_1><b6_0>Algeria<b6_0/><a1_1/><a1_0/>. Founded as a broad Islamist coalition in <a2_0><a2_1><a2_2><b7_0>1989<b7_0/><a2_2/><a2_1/><a2_0/> it was led by Abbassi Madani, and a charismatic Islamist young preacher, Ali Belhadj.
